It is through the efforts of this sort – through the growth and deepening of Latin American 
civil society -- that we can be sure the garbage men will actually arrive in Macondo to clear 
away the refuse strewn across the town, that Big Mama’s rotting corpse will actually stay 
buried, and that, above all, a more just social order will actually be built to replace the one 
she represented. 
 
